article.description: Bosha has 19; Lamar rolls over Central Arkansas 84-65
article.headline: Bosha has 19; Lamar rolls over Central Arkansas 84-65
article.linkText: Bosha has 19; Lamar rolls over Central Arkansas 84-65
article.story: BEAUMONT, Texas -- Zjori Bosha made 5 of 8 from beyond the arc to score 19 points as Lamar rolled over winless Central Arkansas 84-65 on Saturday night. Bosha, who tied his career high for points, made 7 of 10 field goal attempts and had four steals. Kevin Booze had 14 points, Anthony Holliday added 13 and Tyran de Lattibeaudiere chipped in 11 for Lamar (8-7, 2-1 Southland Conference). Lattibeaudiere drove for a layup to break open a tight game and start a 14-2 run midway in the first half. Central Arkansas could not answer and the Cardinals drove to a 52-29 lead at the break. Lamar, which made 8 of 21 3-point attempts, made 34 of 64 shots from the floor while limiting Central Arkansas to 22-of-46 shooting. The Cardinals had 14 steals and 22 assists. Mike Martin scored 14, Jordan Howard had 13 and Ethan Lee contributed 12 for Central Arkansas (0-14, 0-3).
